<subSubSection id="C36D6511FFB9FF91FF3B7340D238FCBC" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC8369AFFB9FF91FF3B7340D238FCBC" blockId="65.[151,1437,783,1062]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
REMARKS.—This is another small species but largest of the Ecuadorian 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D19FFB9FF91FC1A7340D401FCE7" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[950,1041,784,809]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Herrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903EA88FFB9FF91FC1A7340D401FCE7" box="[950,1041,784,809]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Herrera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (body length 16.05–17.95) that can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D19FFB9FF91FE517364D2BFFC80" authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="2020" box="[509,687,820,846]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Herrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polygramma">
<emphasis id="B903EA88FFB9FF91FE517364D2BFFC80" box="[509,687,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">H. polygramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
quickly by the reduced dorsal markings and green venter and 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D19FFB9FF91FA2D7364D137FCBC" authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Herrera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropercula">
<emphasis id="B903EA88FFB9FF91FA2D7364D137FCBC" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">H. nigropercula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the green opercula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
